            <docTitle>
               <titlePart>THE ANCYENT MARINER,<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <hi>a poet’s
                                             reverie.</hi>
               </titlePart>
            </docTitle>
         </titlePage>
         <argument xml:id="ARGUrm">
            <head>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>ARGUMENT.</head>
            <p> How a Ship having first sailed to the Equator, <lb/>was driven by
                                   Storms to the cold Country towards the <lb/>South Pole : How the
                                   Ancient Mariner, cruelly and in con-<lb/>tempt of the Laws of
                                   Hospitality, killed a Sea-bird ; and how he was followed by many
                                   and strange Judgments ; and <lb/>in what Manner he came back to
                                   his own Country.</p>
         </argument>
